PrecisAuthority to enter into the CANADA-NOVA SCOTIA COOPERATION AGREEMENT FOR FORESTRY DEVELOPMENT (1991-1995) which provides for the implementation of cost-shared programs designed to increase the supply of timber, to support sustainable development and integrated resource management through research and technology transfer initiatives, and to enhance public awareness of the importance of forest resources.
